Bison Midstream, LLC: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 9:50 PM ET
Oil, Gas and Consumable Fuels

Company Overview of Bison Midstream, LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Bison Midstream, LLC owns and operates natural gas pipelines and compressor stations. The company was incorporated in 2013 and is based in Denver, Colorado. As of June 4, 2013, Bison Midstream, LLC operates as a subsidiary of Summit Midstream Partners, LP.


999 18th StreetSuite 3400Denver, CO 80202-2434United StatesFounded in 2013



Phone: 720-452-6220








Key Executives for Bison Midstream, LLC


Bison Midstream, LLC does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



Bison Midstream, LLC Key Developments

Bison Midstream Announces Unaudited Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Operating Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2015
Aug 6 15
Bison Midstream announced unaudited earnings results for the second quarter and operating results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2015. Adjusted EBITDA totaled $4.7 million for the second quarter of 2015, down 1.4% from the second quarter of 2014 primarily due to lower margins associated with percent-of-proceeds contracts, partially offset by 13.3% higher volume throughput in the second quarter of 2015 compared to the second quarter of 2014. Adjusted EBITDA for the second quarter of 2015 also benefitted from the aforementioned decision to discontinue allocating certain corporate overhead expenses beginning in the first quarter of 2015. 

For the quarter, average daily throughput was 17 MMcf/d against 15 MMcf/d a year ago. 

For the six months, average daily throughput was 18 MMcf/d against 14 MMcf/d a year ago.


